President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Vermont and has ordered Federal assistance to aid in the recovery efforts following a severe storm and flooding that occurred from October 31 to November 1, 2019. The Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected counties include Addison, Chittenden, Essex, Franklin, Lamoille, Orange, Orleans, and Washington Counties. Additionally, Federal funding will also be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. James R. McPherson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future if requested by the State and based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.